          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Radio Consumer Protection Act of 2017</strong></p> <p>This bill establishes the Radio Consumer Protection Fund through FY2022 to make payments to a broadcast radio station for costs that the station incurred resulting from the reorganization of the broadcast television spectrum.</p> <p>The Federal Communications Commission shall expedite applications from broadcast radio station licensees seeking to obtain special temporary authority to continue broadcasting during the reorganization.</p>]]></text>
